Support us

How can I support the organisation?

   Electriciens sans frontières welcomes all forms of support: donations,
   memberships, communication opportunities...
   Support us
   380 million
   people do not have access to an improved water source
   1.1 billion
   people do not have access to electricity
   80%
   of the populations live in isolated rural areas

FIND OUT ABOUT US

Electriciens sans frontières

   Electriciens sans frontières is a French international NGO and
   registered charity.

   Since 1986 it has been leading projects designed to give access to
   electricity and water for the poorest people to improve their living
   conditions by making access to electricity a lever for human and
   economic development.
   WHO ARE WE?
   CONTACT US

Volunteer

   1,200 volunteers spread throughout France mobilize their time and life
   skills for the NGO’s projects.

Community services

   The NGO prioritizes the electrification of public services to make
   access to electricity a first step towards development.

Sustainability

   Training local actors and creating income-generating activities ensure
   the sustainability of the NGO’s projects.

Renewable energies

   Over 80% of the NGO’s projects use renewable energy, either partially
   or totally.
   Madagascar

Projet

Ambalavao: Water and sanitation

   The inhabitants of the outlying districts of Ambalavao had to go to the
   city centre to draw water from the municipal fountains, which meant
   they had to wsait a long time. The municipal water supply network
   worked for only 7 months out of 12. The rest of the year, the whole
   population drew water from an extremely polluted river.
   Voir le projet
   Haiti
   South Haiti: Refurbishment and support for schools damaged by Hurricane
   Matthew
   Philippines
   Mandaue: Electrification and securing the Red Cross logistics base
   Benin
   Dodji Alixo: Electricity for the “Throne of Wisdom” school
   Senegal
   M’Bomboye: Solar electrification of primary school
   Madagascar
   Andranovelona: training of urban youths in agriculture

All types of skills are welcome at Electriciens sans frontières. I am living
proof!

   Testimony
   I found out about Electriciens sans frontières through my company,
   which is a partner of ESF. The first way in which I helped was by
   writing press releases and creating promotional posters. Today, I am
   part of the team that leads the Lighting for Schools project in
   Senegal, for which I make use of my communication skills. All types of
   skills are welcome at Electriciens sans frontières. I am living proof!

Marion Alberny

Volunteer

At this time of social and environmental responsibility it is quite natural
and logical that we should join forces with Electriciens sans frontières.

   Testimony
   At this time of social and environmental responsibility it is quite
   natural and logical that our Group, which specializes in the design,
   construction and maintenance of electricity transmission and
   distribution infrastructures, should join forces with Electriciens sans
   frontières in order to promote actions of international solidarity
   aimed at giving the poorest populations access to energy, which is
   essential for their development. Our desire is to commit ourselves in a
   sustainable way and to support concrete projects for which we wish to
   mobilize our collaborators as well as providing financial support.
   Skills sponsorship seems to us to be a unifying means to achieve this
   and to respond to the humanitarian impulse inspired by ESF's
   volunteers.

Pascal Schuster

President of SAG France

I chose to give a few euros to ESF in order to allow millions of individuals
around the world also to benefit from electricity

   Testimony
   Have you spent a day, maybe even two or three without the Electricity
   Fairy? Think hard, imagine situations in which you couldn't survive
   without her. Very soon you would be down or your knees, praying for the
   Good Fairy. Praying that she would appear with her magic wand and bring
   life back to your life. I imagined these situations and my imagination
   was stimulated by the very beautiful Electriciens sans frontières'
   documentary "The Electricity Fairy (La Fée Électricité)". I felt I
   needed to match my imagination with the way that I lived and so I chose
   to change my habits to save this energy and to give a few euros to ESF
   in order to allow millions of individuals around the world also to
   benefit from this Good Fairy Electricity.

Marie-Pascale Laurent

Donor

